Being self-driven, self-organized and working with little supervision towards a common team and company purpose.

About the project
Our client and partner is growing their Data Platform team and looking for a talented Senior Data Engineer. In this position, you will contribute to architecture and development of the platform that collects data which is used to help people have amazing, safe trips, as they travel the world.

The client is a very well-known user-generated travel platform – you’ve probably surfed their website while looking for a holiday retreat!

The Data Platform team are the data landscape experts, building out and maintaining truths to enable the company to empower travelers across the world in finding the best hotels, restaurants, and generally great experiences.


Job requirements
3+ years of experience with general software development;
Solid experience developing complex ETL processes (including defining SLA, performance measurements and monitoring);
Experience working with large datasets (terabyte scale and growing);
Familiarity with various technologies and tooling associated with databases and big data;
Know-how of Relational DB (MS SQL, PostgreSQL/MySQL)
Knowledge of best practices around DB administration
Experience with Big Data (i.e. Hadoop, Hive, BigQuery, Snowflake)
Strong experience in OO or functional programming in Java/Python or equivalent language;
Very good Software Engineering principles;
Systems performance and tuning experience, with an eye for how systems architecture and design impacts performance and scalability
Proven record of mentoring junior members of the team & technical leadership on medium to large size projects;
Previous experience in providing innovation via non-trivial solutions to day-to-day problems;
An organized, detail-oriented person who is a natural self-motivator;
Possessing the ability to work in a fast-paced and dynamic environment;
Strong interpersonal skills, intense curiosity, and an enthusiasm for solving difficult problems;
Able to work with end users to solve technical challenges;
Great communication and English language skills.
Hadoop

PostgresSQL

Python

MySQL

Microsoft SQL Server

Java

Responsibilities
As part of this team, the Senior Data Engineer will be responsible for building out all the core datasets that will be used across the company, as well as supporting the analytics, data science, and machine learning teams.


Extra skills
Exposure to and/or interest in machine learning and data science (specifically to help solve day-to-day problems and reach objectives in an innovative way);
Experience working with Apache Airflow or similar systems;
Comfortable working in a Linux CLI environment;
Experience in designing high-scale, fault-tolerant and performant distributed applications.

Requirements:
MS or Ph.D. in Computer Science, Statistics, Information Systems or related quantitative field degree;
3-5+ years of experience as a Data Engineer;
Advanced SQL knowledge and experience working with relational databases;
Experience in building data pipelines: moving data from one database to another, using ETL tools like MATILLION, extracting data from one API to the database, etc.;
2+ years experience with scripting languages such as Ruby /Python.
Nice-to-haves:
Experience with other languages like Java, R, Perl, PHP, and shell scripts;
Experience with Snowflake/Looker;
Experience with scraping;
Experience with filesystems, server architectures, and distributed systems;
Experience with AWS.
Responsibilities:
Design, Build and Maintain the pipelines used to source data at Obviously. This includes integrating with 3rd party APIs and high-scale building/maintaining in house scrapers;
Develop, construct, test, and maintain architectures and analytics tools that utilize the data pipeline to provide actionable business insights;
Identify ways to improve data reliability, efficiency, quality, and scalability;
Organize data for predictive and prescriptive modeling;
Work with stakeholders including the Product, Development, and Design teams to assist with data-related technical issues and support their data infrastructure needs;
Put in place solid data governance and data monitoring infrastructure;
Develop data reports for stakeholders to facilitate the flow of information throughout the company.
